ygData.msgSnippet: I can relate to this too.  Could it be that Hell levels dont exist anymore? Im in 45. This morning I got 2 blue bubbles in 45 in less then an hour and half.
ygData.messageBody:
I can relate to this too. Could it be that Hell levels dont exist anymore?
Im in 45. This morning I got 2 blue bubbles in 45 in less then an hour and
half. And half of that time i spent screwing around dot kiting and then
headed to karnors into captain group with a full group (all of which had
many levels higher then me).

Minkin

Probably seems that way, because you're used to the usual crawl. Maybe once
you're used to this, it too, will seem painfully slow. :)

Just a thought...heh.

Atonal

-----Original Message-----
From: Robert(Bob) Smith [mailto:rws1111@...]
Sent: Thursday, January 18, 2001 9:52 AM
To: eqbards@egroups.com
Subject: [eqbards] Unpopular view...


I played in Karnors last night with a warrior, cleric, monk, and
ranger... all I have to say is I earned as much exp in the two hours
I was there last night as I had in 6+ hour camps before (and the
group was not any better.)

Does anyone else think maybe the exp is now coming too fast?


Gaelthorne
